cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with defending deep neural networks (DNNs) from adversarial attacks, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture for DNNs, which involves feature extraction and defense mechanisms, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the security aspect of DNNs, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper uses deep learning techniques to defend against adversarial attacks, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
